PN,31204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1774314171
OL,3,CGlobal climate is in a 'state of
OL,4,Cemergency', UN Secretary-General warns
OL,6,F2024 was found to be the warmest year
OL,7,Fon record. This was partly driven by
OL,8,Fthe warming "el nino" weather
OL,9,Fphenomenon.
OL,11,FWhile the world is now seeing cooler
OL,12,F"el nina" conditions, forecasters
OL,13,Frecently warned that another "el nino"
OL,14,Fpeak could be seen towards the end of
OL,15,F2026.
OL,17,FWMO scientist John Kennedy said: "If
OL,18,Fwe transition to el nino, we will see
OL,19,Fan increase in global temperature
OL,20,Fagain, and potentially to record
OL,21,Flevels (in 2027)."
OL,26,@pD@MOUpD@UO]tD@AOUtD@IO]uD@^OUuD@fO]yD@
