PN,31207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1774314171
OL,3,CGlobal climate is in a 'state of
OL,4,Cemergency', UN Secretary-General warns
OL,6,FWMO secretary-general Celeste Saulo
OL,7,Fsaid: "Human activities are
OL,8,Fincreasingly disrupting the natural
OL,9,Fequilibrium and we will live with
OL,10,Fthese consequences for hundreds and
OL,11,Fthousands of years.
OL,13,F"On a day-to-day basis, our weather
OL,14,Fhas become more extreme."
OL,16,FThe warming of the atmosphere,
OL,17,Fincluding near the Earth's surface,
OL,18,Fwhich is the temperatures that humans
OL,19,Ffeel, represents just 1% of the excess
OL,20,Fenergy, while about 5% is stored in
OL,21,Fthe continental land masses.
OL,26,@oD@GOUuD@AOUvD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
