PN,31208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1774314171
OL,3,CGlobal climate is in a 'state of
OL,4,Cemergency', UN Secretary-General warns
OL,6,FMeanwhile, heat in the ocean stores
OL,7,Fmore than 91% of the excess heat in
OL,8,Fthe Earth's system and was found to
OL,9,Fhave reached a record high in 2025,
OL,10,Fwith its rate of warming more than
OL,11,Fdoubling between the period of 1960-
OL,12,F2005 to 2005-2025.
OL,14,FThe accelerating amount of heat being
OL,15,Fcaptured in the deep ocean means the
OL,16,Fworld is moving to timescales of
OL,17,Fcommitted climate change for
OL,18,Fcenturies, the WMO added.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
